<br>
As an atheist, I don't feel that there is any biblical reason or religious reason for staying home. I stay home with my kids because it is our choice, as a married couple, and because I am truly happy doing so. I have good friends who are truly happy working. I respect both sides. I think there are so many factors- mom's temperment, finances, goals.....they all have to be taken into account to see what works for each family.  We are very fortunate that there is no need for me to work financially, and tempermentally, I seem to be holding up just fine (no need for the funny farm yet)....<br>
<br>
I always wanted to be a mom. It was my goal in life, and when I started dating my husband, he confessed that he wanted his wife to stay home with the kids. So it was a match for us....;-)<br>
<br>
