I've friends who have told me they couldn't do my job. They have to get out of the house and work for their sanity and for a sense of purpose. I don't blame them. There are days when DH has to remind me that I don't have to refer to myself in third person to him. <br>
<br>
I would love for society to be more accepting of our choices, SAH or working. But it seems no matter what you decide its damned if you do or damned if you don't. What pisses me off though are other mothers who make judgements on you and what you do. I've been looked down at by other working mothers and I've seen my working mother friends looked down at by die hard (sorry but this is my observation) bible thumping sahms. <br>
<br>
I am going to attempt to find a preschool for my child when she turns 3. I want a little one on one time with my younger time and I MIGHT start looking into going back to school earlier then orginally planned - was going to go when they start school, but I could use the mental stimultion.<br>
<br>
The boards are great. I would go brain-dead if not for them. <br>
