<br>
and then I slap myself out of it.<br>
<br>
I quit my job 3 years ago because we were trying to get pregnant, and it wasn't happening so I set out to eliminate the added stress in my life.  Turns out on my last day of work, I was 2 weeks pregnant.<br>
<br>
I was like Emmy, I love the control and &quot;power&quot; that I had when I was working...I was good at what I did, my boss knew it, and my co-workers knew it...they thought I was nuts to leave a promising career in the banking system to be &quot;mom&quot;...but there is nothing else that I have ever been able to see myself doing as a career other than &quot;mom&quot;  <br>
<br>
I was &quot;called&quot; to be a mom, if you will.  I know that, and I remind myself of that when I begin to get the crazy thoughts of going back to work.  (That and the thought of someone else raising my son for the majority of the day just doesn't cut it with me.)<br>
