<br>
The church does encourage mothers to sah whenever possible.<br>
<br>
The church really is a good support...not just for sahm's, but for families in general. The women have their own Sunday class, we have meetings/activities 1 evening a month, there are often playgroups, etc. Husbands are encouraged to support their wives in these activities. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Each woman is assigned a &quot;Visiting Teacher&quot; who visits you monthly. Likewise, you are someone elses visiting teacher.<br>
We have moved a lot, but we always feel we have a home at church. It's the same, every where in the world. The programs are the same, the lesson/study materials are the same...same church, just different people each time. They are a wonderful support for families. Last year, my dh was laid off from his job, i was 10 weeks from delivering our 4th baby, and they helped us so much. They threw me a beautiful baby shower, they provided groceries and diapers for us for 9months <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , They helped us at Christmas with a &quot;little extra something&quot;.....I couldn't say enough good things here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Paige<br>
